generate .raw image from qemu .img file with `qemu-img convert $image.img -O raw $out.raw`
kpartx (from multipath-tools) can mount .raw images
mount /dev/mapper/loop0p1 /mnt

- virsh
    - list


Ungrab mouse: Ctrl+Alt+g

Command to boot usb stick:
sudo qemu-system-x86_64 --enable-kvm -drive file=/dev/sdb,media=disk -m 2G -net nic -net user -cpu host -vga cirrus
